node.text:
Did you know that when welcoming a new doggo into your home, it might take up to 90 days for your new best friend to fully adjust? Our friends at ACANA Pet Foods have created the perfect pet food recipe for helping newly-adopted-pups transition into their forever homes and new diet. 
Not only is ACANA Rescue Care for Adopted Dogs made with top quality, fresh and raw ingredients, according to
Harlow, it is the tastiest kibble she has ever had! 
Each batch is also made with Chamomile and Omega 3&6 fatty acids which can work wonders for skin and coat health. Our dogs love it and even better, so do our foster pups!
Lastly, for every bag of ACANA Rescue Care for Adopted Dogs purchased, a meal is provided to a pet in need. How cool is that?! 
Visit the link in our bio to learn more and other tips on helping your new dog adjust!
#AcanaPartner #AcanaFamily #ACANAforRescues

node.text:
Our dogs (and their cats) spend A LOT of time outside during the summer, which is why we are so excited to be partnering with @SerestoUS! (Although Harlow and Ezra prefer playtime with all four paws on the ground!)

With five dogs and two cats, it is a huge relief to find something to depend on to help protect them from fleas and ticks! Vet-recommended Seresto® is an easy-to-use, odorless collar that repels fleas and ticks for 8 continuous months. 

Talk to your veterinarian about Seresto® for your furry best friend today. Veterinarians are the best source for recommending flea and tick prevention that is right for your pet. 🐶🐱#ad
